AD_Field.Help: Self-Service allows users to enter data or update their data. The flag indicates, that this record was entered or created via Self-Service or that the user can change it via the Self-Service functionality.

AD_Field.Name: Subscription Type
AD_Field.Help: Subscription type and renewal frequency

AD_Field.Name: Drop Shipment
AD_Field.Description: Drop Shipments are sent from the Vendor directly to the Customer
AD_Field.Help: Drop Shipments do not cause any Inventory reservations or movements as the Shipment is from the Vendor's inventory. The Shipment of the Vendor to the Customer must be confirmed.

AD_Field.Name: Product
AD_Field.Help: Identifies an item which is either purchased or sold in this organization.

AD_Field.Name: Active
AD_Field.Description: The record is active in the system
AD_Field.Help: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reports. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for audit purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are invoices for this partner record existing. You de-activate the Business Partner and prevent that this record is used for future entries.

AD_Field.Name: Summary Level
AD_Field.Help: A summary entity represents a branch in a tree rather than an end-node. Summary entities are used for reporting and do not have own values.

AD_Field.Name: Stocked
AD_Field.Help: The Stocked check box indicates if this product is stocked by this Organization.

AD_Field.Name: Purchased
AD_Field.Help: The Purchased check box indicates if this product is purchased by this organization.

AD_Field.Name: Sold
AD_Field.Help: The Sold check box indicates if this product is sold by this organization.

AD_Field.Name: Volume
AD_Field.Help: The Volume indicates the volume of the product in the Volume UOM of the Client

AD_Field.Name: Weight
AD_Field.Help: The Weight indicates the weight of the product in the Weight UOM of the Client

AD_Field.Name: Tax Category
AD_Field.Help: The Tax Category provides a method of grouping similar taxes. For example, Sales Tax or Value Added Tax.

AD_Field.Name: UPC/EAN
AD_Field.Description: Bar Code (Universal Product Code or its superset European Article Number)
AD_Field.Help: Use this field to enter the bar code for the product in any of the bar code symbologies (Codabar, Code 25, Code 39, Code 93, Code 128, UPC (A), UPC (E), EAN-13, EAN-8, ITF, ITF-14, ISBN, ISSN, JAN-13, JAN-8, POSTNET and FIM, MSI/Plessey, and Pharmacode)

AD_Field.Name: Shelf Width
AD_Field.Help: The Shelf Width indicates the width dimension required on a shelf for a product

AD_Field.Name: Shelf Height
AD_Field.Help: The Shelf Height indicates the height dimension required on a shelf for a product

AD_Field.Name: Shelf Depth
AD_Field.Help: The Shelf Depth indicates the depth dimension required on a shelf for a product

AD_Field.Name: Units Per Pallet
AD_Field.Help: The Units per Pallet indicates the number of units of this product which fit on a pallet.

AD_Field.Name: Discontinued
AD_Field.Description: This product is no longer available
AD_Field.Help: The Discontinued check box indicates a product that has been discontinued.

AD_Field.Name: Discontinued At
AD_Field.Description: Discontinued At indicates Date when product was discontinued

AD_Field.Name: Document Note
AD_Field.Help: The Document Note is used for recording any additional information regarding this product.

AD_Field.Name: Comment/Help
AD_Field.Help: The Help field contains a hint, comment or help about the use of this item.

AD_Field.Name: Classification
AD_Field.Help: The Classification can be used to optionally group products.

AD_Field.Name: Company Agent
AD_Field.Help: Purchase agent for the document. Any Sales Rep must be a valid internal user.

AD_Field.Name: Revenue Recognition
AD_Field.Help: The Revenue Recognition indicates how revenue will be recognized for this product

AD_Field.Name: Bill of Materials
AD_Field.Help: The Bill of Materials check box indicates if this product consists of a bill of materials.

AD_Field.Name: Print detail records on invoice
AD_Field.Description: Print detail BOM elements on the invoice
AD_Field.Help: The Print Details on Invoice indicates that the BOM element products will print on the Invoice as opposed to this product.

AD_Field.Name: Print detail records on pick list
AD_Field.Description: Print detail BOM elements on the pick list
AD_Field.Help: The Print Details on Pick List indicates that the BOM element products will print on the Pick List as opposed to this product.

AD_Field.Name: Verified
AD_Field.Description: The BOM configuration has been verified
AD_Field.Help: The Verified check box indicates if the configuration of this product has been verified. This is used for products that consist of a bill of materials

AD_Field.Name: Verify BOM Structure
AD_Field.Help: The Verify BOM process checks for circular BOMs (unsupported).

AD_Field.Name: Image URL
AD_Field.Help: URL of image; The image is not stored in the database, but retrieved at runtime. The image can be a gif, jpeg or png.

AD_Field.Name: Mail Template
AD_Field.Help:
The Mail Template indicates the mail template for return messages. Mail text can include variables. The priority of parsing is User/Contact, Business Partner and then the underlying business object (like Request, Dunning, Workflow object).
So, @Name@ would resolve into the User name (if user is defined defined), then Business Partner name (if business partner is defined) and then the Name of the business object if it has a Name.
For Multi-Lingual systems, the template is translated based on the Business Partner's language selection.

AD_Field.Help: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

AD_Field.Name: Attribute Set
AD_Field.Help: Define Product Attribute Sets to add additional attributes and values to the product. You need to define a Attribute Set if you want to enable Serial and Lot Number tracking.

AD_Field.Name: UOM
AD_Field.Help: The UOM defines a unique non monetary Unit of Measure

AD_Field.Name: Product Type
AD_Field.Help: The type of product also determines accounting consequences.
